        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 6:33PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 632 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Woodville, or 12 miles west of Scottsboro, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Scottsboro, Grant, Gurley, Woodville, Langston, Paint Rock, Lim Rock,
Garth, Larkinsville, and Hampton Cove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
